item.description:
Meet at 9:00 and should leave Dunks by 9:30 or so..to arrive in time for those of you who want to attend Bike Blessing..

Hi, I am going to attend this; I know there are a few off on their week long trek so if anyone is interested please let me know. We can meet and ride in together. I did this last year and it is well organized...feet up all the way... Sunday, June 26 · 9:00am - 12:00pm Location WHITMAN VFW, POST 697, 95 ESSEX STREET, WHITMAN, MA. Starting Sunday, 6/26/2011, NEXT YEARS SPECIAL PROJECT WILL BE "THE WOUNDED WARRIOR PROJECT" Everyone is invited to a great Event! 2 Wheels,4 Wheels, Walk or Ride ~ but don't miss a great time! $15.00 per person; Rider, Passenger or Walk In 9:30A.M. ~ 10:30A.M. REGISTRATION FOR RUN 10:30a.m. Blessing of the Bikes & Riders by "The Covenant Ministry" 10:45a.m. Kickstands Up for a South Shore backroads ride NOON Cook out starts ~ Live Band "The Back Nine" Professional Photographer ~ 5x7 @ $10.each The Famous "Eagle Eye Painting" to paint your bike! Motorcycle Parts Vendor, Tshirt Vendor, Etc. Something for everyone! All Proceeds will go to the Wounded Warrior Project.
